.RE
.PP
PAM_SUCCESS
.RS 4
Success\&.
.RE
.PP
PAM_USER_UNKNOWN
.RS 4
User not known\&.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
Add the following line to
/etc/pam\&.d/login
to indicate that the user has new mail when they login to the system\&.
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
session  optional  pam_mail\&.so standard
      
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
